 <!-- Detailed Analysis -->
 <section class="bg-slate-900/60 rounded-xl shadow-lg p-6 mb-8">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Detailed Analysis</h2>
 
 <div class="mb-8">
 <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Pricing Deep Dive</h3>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">Both platforms start around <strong>$5 per hour</strong>, but their pricing structures differ significantly. See Guru offers a flexible credit system where you pay for what you use. Basic lessons with certified tutors cost around $5 per hour. Premium tutors with specialized expertise run $15-40 per hour.
 </p>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">Preply uses a package model where buying more lessons upfront saves you money. New users often find tutors in the <strong>$5-10 per hour</strong> range. However, the most popular and highly-rated tutors typically charge $15-40 per hour. Preply also requires you to commit to lesson packages, which means less flexibility if your schedule changes.
 </p>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
 <strong>For budget learners who want to practice daily</strong>, See Guru's lower baseline price and affordable lesson rates can offer better value. For those who prefer structured human lessons, Preply's package deals can work out cheaper per session.
 </p>
 </div>

 <div class="mb-8">
 <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Tutor Quality and Experience</h3>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">See Guru's certified human tutors offer 1-on-1 video lessons at affordable rates starting from $5/hr. With a large pool of qualified teachers available across time zones, you can find tutors who match your schedule and learning goals. Each tutor is vetted and holds teaching credentials.
 </p>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">Preply's human tutors bring real-world experience and cultural context to every lesson. They can explain nuances, answer questions about idioms and slang, and provide personalized feedback based on your specific goals. The best tutors on Preply have hundreds of positive reviews and years of teaching experience.
 </p>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
 <strong>Neither approach is objectively better.</strong> If you want consistent practice at affordable rates, See Guru's certified tutors excel. If you value human connection and cultural insights, Preply's tutors may serve you better.
 </p>
 </div>

 <div class="mb-8">
 <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Learning Experience and Results</h3>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">See Guru works best for learners who need to practice regularly at affordable rates. With tutors available across multiple time zones, you can find lessons that fit your schedule. The tutors are patient and supportive. You can repeat topics as many times as you need without feeling embarrassed.
 </p>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">Preply delivers better results for learners who need accountability and structured progress. Having a real person expecting you at a scheduled time creates strong motivation. Human tutors can identify patterns in your mistakes, push you out of your comfort zone, and celebrate your wins with genuine enthusiasm.
 </p>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
 <strong>In our testing</strong>, See Guru users reported higher daily practice frequency but similar long-term progress compared to Preply users who attended weekly lessons. The best approach combines both: use See Guru for daily practice and Preply for weekly structured sessions.
 </p>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- Who Should Choose Which -->
